Plastic waste management is a crucial aspect of environmental sustainability in the present-day scenario. As the global population grows and urbanizes, the production and improper disposal of plastic waste have become a significant concern. The plastic waste management market can be segmented by service, polymer type, source, and end-use industry. The service segment includes collection & transportation, recycling, landfills, and incineration. In terms of polymer type, the market is categorized into polyethylene (PE), polypropylene (PP), polyethylene terephthalate (PET), polyvinyl chloride (PVC), polystyrene (PS), and others. The source segment consists of residential, commercial & institutional, and industrial sectors. Lastly, the end-use industry segment covers packaging, building & construction, textile & clothing, automotive, and other industries.

